                And then fourthly, the spring of all;
Christ both died, and rose againe, that hee
might be Lord both of quick and dead.

Again, Our selves are our greatest enemies.
• here is no such flatterer, as the bosome flatterer. That enemy, selfe, that we have in our bosomes betrayeth us to Satan;
else all the Devils in hell could not hurt us. Self is our own enemy, and Gods enemy. Nay, enemy is too easie, too good a word; the best thing in us, is enmity it self against God.
